Certainly! We can also solve the Longest Palindromic Substring problem using a Dynamic Programming (DP) approach. This method will also yield a time complexity of 
ğ‘‚
(
ğ‘›
2
)
O(n 
2
 ) and a space complexity of 
ğ‘‚
